com.link_intersystems.lang.ref

Class AbstractSerializableReference<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.link_intersystems.lang.ref.AbstractSerializableReference<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - of the wrapped non serializable object.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Reference<T>, SerializableReference<T>, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NullReference

    public abstract class AbstractSerializableReference<T>
extends Object
implements SerializableReference<T>
    A reference to an object that is not serializable but can be restored out of other information (e.g. Class object can be restored from a full qualified class name that is a string).
    Since:
    1.0.0;
